rectly to the alarm system.";i:42;s:47:"Buy a wired garage door sensor from Alarm Grid.";i:43;s:224:"For garage OHD status I typically use the KPs F keys as status indicators no additional hardware needed and since I typically put in KPs and not KP2 or KP3s I tend to use F5 and F6 as an indicator for a normal 2 door garage.";i:44;s:110:"For the LEDs using a bicolored unit you can get 3 colors a typical red green and amber out of the single unit.";i:45;s:157:"A garage door status indicator system that has a controller coupled to a garage door and a remote device remotely located from proximity with the controller.";i:46;s:237:"The system further has a first processor residing on the controller and configured to detect when a garage door is open and transmit an open status signal indicative of the garage being open and a second processor residing on the remote.";}}